<paragraph id="8BA9BC0A8006FFED8616FD8CFBA1DECD" blockId="5.[264,1323,583,689]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
The genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C16C7898006FFED868EFD8CFE09DE1C" box="[400,503,583,608]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Astochia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96260188006FFED868EFD8CFE09DE1C" box="[400,503,583,608]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Astochia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is related to 
<taxonomicName id="4C16C7898006FFED8582FD8CFCE7DE1C" box="[668,793,583,608]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Neoitamus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96260188006FFED8582FD8CFCE7DE1C" box="[668,793,583,608]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Neoitamus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in regards to the elongated ovipositor. The male genitalia (
<figureCitation id="132DA08F8006FFED86DEFDA4FDF6DEF5" box="[448,520,623,649]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 12" captionStartId="25.[264,382,1737,1761]" captionTargetBox="[363,1283,315,1719]" captionTargetId="figure@25.[308,1364,315,1732]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 12. Male external genitalia, lateral views. 1. Aneomochtherus sinensis. 2. Asilella londti. 3. Astochia virgatipes. 4. Eutolmus brevistylus. 5. Machimus aurulentus. 6. Machimus cf. pastshenkoae 7. Mercuriana ussuriensis. 8. Neoitamus angusticornis. 9. Neoitamus castaneipennis. 10. Neoitamus cothurnatus univittatus. 11. Neoitamus zouhari. 12. Philonicus albiceps. Scale bar = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/171901/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
Fig. 
<number id="3DDEAE2D8006FFED86E7FDA4FDF6DEF5" box="[505,520,623,649]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
) with its paralobi (dorsal and apical paired lobes) are distinct from other Korean genera. Fore basitarsus stout and thickened. Head widened.
</paragraph>
